HB 4107-3
(LC 310)
2/5/26 (SCT/ps)
Requested by Representative NATHANSON
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4107
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, delete lines 18 through 24 and insert:
2 “(d) ‘Specialty urgent care center’ means a facility or portion of a facility
3 that provides to individuals, on a walk-in and episodic basis:
4 “(A) For illnesses or injuries that are acute but not life-threatening or
5 that do not require emergency medical services, medical care related only to
6 a specific body system; or
7 “(B) Behavioral health care services only.
8 “(e)(A) ‘Urgent care center’ means a facility or portion of a facility that:
9 “(i) Uses the term ‘urgent’ or ‘urgent care’ to describe the facility or
10 portion of the facility; and
11 “(ii) Provides medical care to individuals only on a walk-in and episodic
12 basis for illnesses or injuries that are acute but not life-threatening or that
13 do not require emergency medical services.”.
14 On page 3, delete line 11 and insert “an emergency department of a hos-
15 pital licensed under ORS 441.025.”.
